  "commentary": "With SPX at 6597.33 sitting between the massive negative gamma wall at 6590 (-36B) and positive gamma wall at 6605 (+40.9B), dealers are currently in a precarious hedging position where any move toward 6590 will force aggressive buying while a push to 6605 triggers selling pressure. The PIN regime confirms dealers are long gamma and will provide stabilizing flow, but the recent regime flip and wall break suggest we just witnessed significant dealer repositioning that could create temporary volatility spikes. Watch 6590 closely as a break below unleashes amplifying dealer buying that could create sharp bounces, while 6605 acts as natural resistance where dealer selling kicks in.\n\nBottom line: expect volatile ping-pong action between 6590 and 6605 with dealers acting as shock absorbers.",
